SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-4-701(c), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting:
(c) Subject to available funding, TSAC shall administer a pilot program to award
a Tennessee Future Teacher scholarship to future educators. The program begins with
the 2023-2024 academic year and terminates on July 1, 2030.
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-4-701(d), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting:
(d) To be eligible for a Tennessee Future Teacher scholarship, an eligible
candidate must:
(1) Be admitted to and enrolled in an approved EPP or a teachers
college at an eligible postsecondary institution, as defined in subdivision
(b)(3)(B);
(2) Complete the scholarship application, as required by TSAC; and
(3) Sign a promissory note agreeing to teach in an LEA or public charter
school in this state for at least two (2) consecutive years in a targeted setting.
SECTION 6. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-4-701(f), is amended by deleting
subdivisions (1) and (2) and substituting:
(1) The student has attained a degree through an approved EPP or a teachers
college at an eligible postsecondary institution, as defined in subdivision (b)(3)(B);
(2) The student no longer meets:
(A) The standards established by the:
(i) State board of education for admission to the student's
approved EPP; or
(ii) Eligible postsecondary institution, as defined in subdivision
(b)(3)(B), for admission to the institution's teachers college; or
(B) The standards of the:
(i) Approved EPP in which the student is enrolled; or
